-- Nigeria to issue 50 bln naira in 3-, 10-year bonds
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Wed Apr 16, 2014 08:53AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, April 16 (Reuters) - Nigeria plans to issue 60 billion naira ($371 million) of 3-year and 10-year sovereign bonds on April 23, its forth monthly auction this year, the Debt Management Office (DMO) said on Wednesday.

The debt office said it will issue 25 billion naira each in the debt notes due for maturity in August 2016 and March 2014. The bonds are a re-opening of previously issued paper.